{{Politics of Namibia}} The '''Democratic Co-operative Party''' ('''DEMKOP'''), was a small local [[political party]] in [[Ovamboland]], [[Namibia]] led by [[Johannes Nangutuuala]]. The party opposed [[South Africa]]n occupation of [[South West Africa]] and joined the [[SWAPO Youth League]] at rallies.{{sfn|Katjavivi|1988|p=74}} Nangutuuala was publicly flogged for his political activism.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://africanactivist.msu.edu/document_metadata.php?objectid=32-130-74 |title=Terror In Namibia |work=African Activist Archive |publisher=[[Michigan State University]] |accessdate=8 July 2013}}</ref> Established in 1973 it was active only for a short while; by 1975 its activities had ceased, and its leader Nangutuuala had taken up work with the South African administration in Ovamboland.{{sfn|Katjavivi|1988|p=94}}
